snippet.textDisplay: My 1st son's due date was November 6th 2016 I had him October 29th 2016 at 11:15 PM I went for my last appointment Wednesday October 26th and my doctor said that I was gonna be induced that Monday which I was gonna be 39 weeks and due to the fact that I had gestational diabetes I couldn't go much longer but my child decided he was gonna come when he wanted to so Friday the 28th which was also my last day of work and started my maternity leave I got home from work that Friday and I sat down on my bed and I notice I was leaking fluids I was like wtf did I just pee on myself thought nothing of it and went to shower after I got out I noticed my undies was wet so I went to the livingroom and told my sister and friend I  was like guys look I think I leed myself I lifted my leg and boom water all over the floor they both got up so quick nervous and was like ok let's go and halfway down the road noticed they left me behind long story short got to the hospital nurse swabbed me and was like congratulations you are in labor so I called my bf he was knocked out so I had to call my suegra and I was like mom I'm in the hospital my water broke just take your time literally 20 min later they were both there mind you they lived about half an hour away 21 hours of labor later my sweet baby boy was born at 7lbs 3 ounces  ( I was a chicken with the pain so I had the epidural man do I regret it now so much back pain)... Just do whatever you feel is right for you and your baby

snippet.textDisplay: I had a shoulder dystocia with my first born (baby girl 8lbs 20in) & for my second baby (boy) I was expecting the same! Aweee ❤️
I remember being a strong and firm believer of natural birth & even if I had another baby I’d probably want to just to experience it. My youngest (daughter) was a scheduled C section scheduled in January (since I had an emergency c section with my son, I basically had no choice). When I was 32 weeks my body went into labor and I dilated to 4cm and got put on bed rest. At 36 weeks I started getting contractions and rushed to the hospital, I was 6cm and her head was crowning I was rushed to surgery. I was sooooo scared she wouldn’t be able to breathe on her own, about an hr later 5lbs 8oz later I heard her cry.

Nothing anybody says about their story or experience or what you should or shouldn’t do will change what God’s plans are, c section or natural birth we still grew a life inside of us that gets to come out and you get to love and raise forever. Good luck tomorrow and may your baby come out with the least stress to him.
